HEADWORD: Serry
<hw>Ser"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Serried</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Serrying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>serrer</ets>, LL.
<ets>serrare</ets>, <ets>serare</ets>, from L. <ets>sera</ets> a bar,
bolt; akin to <ets>serere</ets> to join or bind together. See
<er>Serries</er>.]</ety> <def>To crowd; to press together.</def>
<note>[Now perhaps only in the form <xex>serried</xex>, p. p. or
a.]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

